<h1>Problem 906 - 2007 IMOSL, G3, G</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 6</h2>
<p>The diagonals of a trapezium \(ABCD\) intersect at point \(P\). Point \(Q\) lies between the parallel lines \(BC\) and \(AD\) such that \(\angle AQD = \angle CQB\), and line \(CD\) separates points \(P\) and \(Q\). Prove that \(\angle BQP = \angle DAQ\).</p>
